 covers near-core\nrotation rates from almost zero up to the critical rate. The frequencies of\ntheir identified modes lead to models with stiffness values between $10^{2.69}$\nand $10^{3.60}$ for the B-type pulsators, while those of F-type stars cover the\nrange from $10^{3.47}$ to $10^{4.52}$. The convective Rossby numbers derived\nfrom the maximum convective diffusion coefficient in the convective core, based\non mixing length theory and a value of the mixing length coefficient relevant\nfor these pulsators, vary between $10^{-2.3}$ and $10^{-0.8}$ for B-type stars\nand $10^{-3}$ and $10^{-1.5}$ for F-type stars. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Oct 2021 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 12 Dec 2021 16:10:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-14"}
